# Untold Story - 2D RPG Development Rules

## Project Context
- 2D RPG in Python with pygame-ce
- Monster taming/battling system (DQM + Pokemon inspired)
- Ruhrpott setting with German dialogue using local slang
- Turn-based combat with 12 types, 9 ranks (F-X)

## Code Standards
- Python 3.13.5 with pygame-ce 2.5+
- Use type hints everywhere
- Dataclasses for data structures
- All code/comments in English
- All in-game text in German (Ruhrpott dialect)

## Key Systems
- Grid-based movement (16x16 tiles)
- Battle system with phases: Intro → Input → Execution → Aftermath → End
- Taming system (DQM-style, not pokeballs)
- Party max 6, Storage boxes for extras
- Synthesis system for monster fusion
- Save/Load with JSON→ZIP

## Important Reminders
- Use 'attacker/defender/multiplier' not 'atk/def/x'
- Logical resolution 320×180, scale to 1280×720
- No DQM size system - all monsters take 1 slot
- Resources should be cached
- Fail gracefully when assets missing

## File Structure
- engine/core/ - Game loop, scenes, resources
- engine/systems/ - Game mechanics
- engine/ui/ - UI components  
- engine/world/ - Maps, entities, camera
- data/ - JSON data files
- assets/ - Graphics, audio

## When making changes
- Keep modules focused and split large systems
- Add debug features behind TAB key
- Make systems data-driven via JSON
- Use deterministic RNG for testing
- Always handle edge cases

